Base

Class RunLine

  • java.lang.Object
    • Base.RunLine
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<RunLine>

    public class RunLine
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<RunLine>
    Representation of a single line of a Run file; each line contains:topicID queryID documentID rank score runID this class contains also the NORMALIZED RANK obtained after normalization

    • Constructor Detail

      • RunLine

        public RunLine(java.lang.String globalID,
               RunLineScores scores)
        Class constructor. To build a new RunLine you must give information about query, topic and dcoument (RunLine.GlobalID() and about score and rank they get for the current retrieval (scores).
        Parameters:
        globalID - The global id is the string that includes all RunLine ids. It is build as: globalID = "documentID"+ sep + "queryID" + sep + "topicID" sep is a defined separator
        scores - The score object contains all information about current document scores and rank for curret query and topic.
        See Also:
        sep, RunLineScores, GlobalID()

      • RunLine

        public RunLine(java.lang.String line)
        Class constructor. You can build a RunLine using this constructor for each line of a Terrier run file.
        Parameters:
        line - It is the string containing all RunLine info. The correct format of line is: "topicID" + sep + "queryID" + sep +"documentID"+ sep + "score" + sep + "rank"+ "RunID "

      • getRunAsLine

        public java.lang.String getRunAsLine()
        You can use it to print a RunLine to file in Terrier format.
        Returns:
        The object rappresentation in Terrier run line format. This one is: "topicID" + sep + "queryID" + sep +"documentID"+ sep + "score" + sep + "rank"+ "RunID " It is the same format we use on RunLine(String) constructor to build the object.
        See Also:

        public int compareTo(RunLine runLine)
